<p>What is the solution to <m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{9}={3}{x}+{21}</m>? <fillin characters="3" />Preview Question 1 Â  </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>3</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{9}={3}{x}+{21}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{9}-{21}={3}{x}+{21}-{21}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{12}={3}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{12}-{7}{x}={3}{x}-{7}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12}=-{4}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{12}}{{-{{4}}}}=\frac{{-{4}{x}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}={x}</m>.</p>

</solution>
